[2
Date: Thu, 11 Oct 2001 23:04:37 -0400 (EDT)
From: Philip S Brachman <pbrachm@sph.emory.edu>

And as reported by Carr and Ray in Journal of Infectious Diseases
100;169-171,1957. They cultured 101 employees in two goat hair
processing textile mills and recovered _B. anthracis_ from 7 nasal swabs
and 7 pharyngeal washings all different people who had no symptoms and
worked in the mills. There was some correlation with the degree of
environmental contamination with _B. anthracis_ in each of their work
areas.
--
Philip Brachman
Emory University
Atlanta, GA
<pbrachm@sph.emory.edu>
[Phil researched anthrax in the wool & hair industries in the 1950s &
1960s which are reported in an important series of papers, that are well
worth re-reading today. Thank you Phil. - Mod.MHJ
